OL,3,CCouncil insists special educational
OL,4,Cneeds services for pupils are improving
OL,6,FThe man in charge of delivering
OL,7,Fimprovements to services for pupils in
OL,8,FKent with special educational needs
OL,9,Fhas revealed they have been making
OL,10,Fprogress, but admits there is still
OL,11,Fmore work to do.
OL,13,FITV Meridian has spoken to Councillor
OL,14,FRory Love, Kent County Council's
OL,15,Fcabinet member for Education and
OL,16,FSkills.
OL,18,FIt comes after families said that the
OL,19,Fcurrent provision for children is
OL,20,Fworse than ever.
